</a></p>

            <h3>Trend 5: AI Bond Issuance Wave Faces Resistance as Investor D=
emand Softens</h3>
            <p>Tech giants like Alphabet, Meta, Amazon, and Nvidia have issue=
d over $300 billion in bonds this year to fund AI development. However, recen=
t issuances have faced resistance, with lower order coverage ratios and risin=
g yields.</p>
            <p>The massive supply of corporate debt, combined with high volum=
es of US government debt, has saturated the bond market. As a result, technol=
ogy companies are facing higher borrowing costs to sustain their aggressive A=
I capital expenditures.</p>
            <p class=3D"trend-summary">So What? Rising borrowing costs in the=
 bond market could force tech giants to moderate their capital spending, pote=
ntially slowing down the pace of global AI infrastructure development in the =
medium term.</p>
