            <h3>Trend 1: International AI Ethics Governance Action Plan Relea=
sed at WAIC 2026</h3>
            <p>An international action plan on AI ethics governance was offic=
ially released at the 2026 World AI Conference in Shanghai. Developed under U=
N frameworks, the plan calls for ethical governance throughout the entire AI =
lifecycle.</p>
            <p>The plan emphasizes categorized risk prevention, agile governa=
nce, and the protection of vulnerable groups. For financial institutions, thi=
s framework provides a clear roadmap for aligning their AI deployments with i=
nternational ethical and compliance standards.</p>
            <p class=3D"trend-summary">So What? The release of this global ac=
tion plan signals a coordinated effort to standardize AI ethics, forcing mult=
inational banks to implement rigorous compliance checks and explainability st=
andards for their financial algorithms.</p>
            <p><a href=3D"http://www.szdaily.com/content/2026-07/20/content_3=
2126122.htm">Read more</a></p>
           =20
            <h3>Trend 2: Australia to Legislate AI Regulation Focusing on Cop=
yright Protection</h3>
            <p>The Australian government has announced plans to introduce a n=
